## Hard rules — never break
1. Never read `localStorage`, `window`, or `document` at module scope or in `useState` initializers — use `useEffect` or server-side patterns.
2. Never expose server-only values (tokens, secrets) to Client Components.
3. All database access goes through the documented client — no raw SQL outside of migrations.
4. Every route that touches user data must verify the session before any DB call.
